               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17310115-29-person188">
                  Mary 
                  Adams 
               <interp inst="t17310115-29-person188" type="surname" value="Adams"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310115-29-person188" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310115-29-person188" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That the Prisoner came to her Room, forc'd open the Door, came in upon her, and told her he wanted Money, and Money he would have, and took the Pen-case, with two Notes in it, and 2 Guineas, and went away, which Notes the Prisoner's Wife said he had burnt; that when her Son, 
               <persName id="t17310115-29-person189">
                  John 
                  Pool 
               <interp inst="t17310115-29-person189" type="surname" value="Pool"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310115-29-person189" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310115-29-person189" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , came home, she inform'd him of what the Prisoner had done, that thereupon he went out that Afternoon, and apprehended the Prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17310115-29-person190">
                  John 
                  Pool 
               <interp inst="t17310115-29-person190" type="surname" value="Pool"></interp>
